These days will take the place of inservice days previously scheduled in October and March, so the school year will end on the same day, tentatively June 17th. Check out the year-at-a-glance calendar at the link below.

We have been informed of two program interruptions tonight for viewers of Channel 19: the graduation ceremony did not air until 7 pm and then a technical issue caused the recording to stop, and restart back to the beginning. We apologize for these disruptions in what was a very meaningful ceremony to many viewers.
If you would like to view the ceremony in its entirety again, it will air on Channel 19 again at noon, 3 pm, 6 pm and 9 pm for the next week, beginning on Thursday, June 18th. It will also remain available on the Pemberton Township Schools YouTube Channel for your viewing pleasure.
Congratulations Class of 2020!

SCHOOL MEALS AVAILABLE DURING SCHOOL CLOSURE

Pemberton Township Schools will be making FREE breakfast and lunch available to ALL students during our mandated school closure. Beginning Monday March 16th, bagged, take-home meals will be dispersed at the following locations Monday through Friday, between the hours of 9 am and 1 pm:

Busansky Elementary School: 16 Scrapetown Road
Denbo Elementary School: 1412 Junction Road
Stackhouse Elementary School: 125 Trenton Road Bldg 1
Pemberton Early Childhood Education Center: 100 Arney's Mt.

Families driving to the site are asked to stay in their vehicles as staff members bring the meals to them, and walkers are asked to go to the glass vestibule in the main lobby to pick up their meals. Names are required to receive the meals, and staff members will sign in all recipients. To aid in efficiency, we will distribute both breakfast and lunch meals at the same time.

Please contact our food services department with any questions at 609-893-5788.

CORONAVIRUS UPDATE MARCH 12, 2020:
This afternoon Governor Phil Murphy recommended that all public gatherings of over 250 people should be cancelled in NJ. To that end, we are postponing all upcoming district events through spring break, April 20th, including the Middle School play, Instrumental and Fine Arts Festival and District Jazz Band Festival. All field trips are cancelled as well, as is outside organization use of our facilities. Interscholastic sports will continue until further notice, and your school principal will share any other individual school event cancellations with you. As of today, our schools are remaining OPEN, but we are continuing to monitor the situation very closely and will contact you with any information should that change. Please know that the health and well-being of our students, staff and community remains our highest priority. Thank you for your cooperation and patience as we navigate through this together.
Go to our district homepage and click on the red arrow for continual updates: https://www.pemberton.k12.nj.us

post_text:
A MESSAGE FROM OUR SUPERINTENDENT REGARDING STATE FUNDING:
Yesterday, February 27th, the New Jersey Department of Education released the numbers for school state aid for the 2020-2021 school year, and Pemberton Township Schools’ state aid was reduced by $4.6 million.

While we have been preparing for this possibility since last August, now that the numbers have become an actuality, we must move forward in implementing these reductions.

Please know that even as we move forward in making reductions, we are continuing to fight for fair funding. We have sent letters to the governor, the commissioner of education and various legislators in an effort to draw attention to what we believe is a major flaw in the state’s calculations for fiscal year 2021. In addition, we are working closely with the Educational Law Center, who strongly supports our position, and we will keep you informed of our progress.

As always, our goal is to be able to maintain quality staffing and comprehensive programs to provide our students with the thorough and efficient education they deserve.

post_text: School State Aid was released today, and we were disappointed to see the 2018 state average tax rate used for calculating municipal overburden. We respectfully request the state revisit FY21 calculations using the 2019 state average tax rate. The state has witnessed the negative impact static school aid calculation has had on NJ schools in recent years. Pemberton will continue to advocate for fair funding.

post_text: Monday, December 9th: All afterschool activities at Denbo School, including WACC & SACC and 21st Century, are cancelled for this afternoon due to a power outage. The building had a partial power outage this morning which required the utility company to shut down all power to work on the issue. Lunches and water were served, a generator was brought in to power heat and bathrooms, and a team of security and administrators were onsite to ensure the safety and comfort of all students. We thank students and staff for their cooperation and patience and expect power to be restored for normal operations tomorrow, December 10th.
